value.value: Adult ascending neuron with bilateral VNC arbors (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a secondary neuron of the 05B hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Within the VNC it fasciculates with the ventral median tract of ventral cervical fasciculus (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in multiple regions and sends output to multiple regions (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is gaba (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 7 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
